    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="624" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d624">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1891</hi>.</date>
                                (Received March 30.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 175.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Yesterday I sent you the following
                            telegram in cipher.<note n="*" xml:id="d624fn1">For telegram see
                                telegram from Mr. Whitehouse of March 15.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Although convinced that every possible measure was being taken by our
                            Government for the protection of Italians, I forwarded the above at the
                            earnest request of the under secretary of foreign affairs, who called
                            upon me immediately after the news of this lamentable affair reached
                            Rome and urged that some such representation should be made.</p>
                <p>This morning I called upon Minister di Rudini, minister of foreign
                            affairs, and expressed to him my horror at the assassinations and the
                            conviction that the President and the people of the United States would
                            deeply lament the same and were taking energetic measures for the
                            protection of Italians.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. G. Porter</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
